--[[
    HOW IT WORKS
    ─────────────
    • Type a fake player name in the text box, press "Start Trade"
    • A simulated trade window opens — visually mirrors the real one
    • "You" (Local) and the fake other player each have a mock inventory
    • Click [+] to open the inventory picker and add items to your side
    • "Simulate Other" buttons let you drive the other player's actions
      (add random item, remove last item, accept, decline)
    • Accept flow: both sides must accept → 3-second countdown → trade
      executes (or either side can unaccept / decline before it fires)
    • All state is local — nothing touches the server or real data

    FAKE INVENTORY
    ──────────────
    Edit FAKE_INVENTORY below to match your game's item types / names.
    Each entry: { name, emoji, value, stackable, amt (optional) }
--]]

